summary: genuine anecdote: when I was standing up at the end of Infinity War, the girl who sat next to me asked aloud what was the logo...
body:
genuine anecdote: when I was standing up at the end of Infinity War, the girl who sat next to me asked aloud what was the logo that just appeared on Fury’s device, and I told her that it was Captain Marvel’s symbol, a new upcoming superhero. She went ‘Oh, another one…’ with kind of a deception in her voice (she used the French word to say ‘another’ in a default masculine way) so I replied ‘It’s gonna be a girl!’ 

And she suddenly BEAMED like ‘It’s gonna be a WOMAN?!’ and her friend went ‘Captain of Marvel is a woman??’ and I nodded and they both had big smiles and light in their eyes it was amazing

summary: I still think Marvel missed a huge opportunity never given G. Willow Wilson the Captain Marvel ongoing book. With her writing...
body:
I still think Marvel missed a huge opportunity never given G. Willow Wilson the Captain Marvel ongoing book. With her writing Ms. Marvel as long as she did there would’ve been even better synchronization with their relationship as Carol mentors her and the growth of Kamala as a hero. I really liked their friendship and wanted more. Even though Civil War II shattered that for a while. 

Oh well, what I want isn’t important. Both Carol and Kamala are getting new creative teams and most likely they’ll only interact in passing. Kamala doesn’t need Carol as a mentor much these days, but still I hope writers don’t forget that they are friends. Or that Kamala is an Inhuman and she is friends with many Inhumans. Maybe just stop forgetting about the Inhumans, Marvel.

summary: Meet my two year old cat named Goose (short for Gustavo). We both just found out that Carol Danvers’ orange cat will be named...
body: Meet my two year old cat named Goose (short for Gustavo). We both just found out that Carol Danvers’ orange cat will be named Goose in the Captain Marvel movie. Am I now convinced that I am Carol Danvers? Quite possibly. Everyone please take a moment of silence out of respect for Goose, who has predicted a gigantic flood of cat adopting and Goose-namings after the release of this movie.
